Etymology. Pyotr Kuzmich Kozlov (Russian: Пётр Кузьмич Козлов;
1863–1935
) is an illustrious Russian investigator of Central Asia, participated and led 6 long term expeditions to Mongolia and China ; geographer and archeologist. A knowledgeable zoologist, he had accumulated abundant and diverse collections including many insects.
